Pre-Game Insights: Mali heads into their upcoming match against Eswatini as clear favorites, despite the potential absence of three key players: Amadou Diallo, Mousa Sylla, and Haidara Traore.
Diallo has been instrumental in Mali’s recent campaigns, while Sylla’s solid performance and Traore’s threat have made them pivotal figures.
Mali’s recent form has been shaky, with their last two matches ending in frustrating stalemates.
Eswatini approaches the match as underdogs and will look to take advantage of the pressure on the Malian side.
